WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:06.390 --> 00:00:09.590
'Tis time for torture, Princess.

3
00:00:10.430 --> 00:00:12.140
Today's torture is...

4
00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:14.900
Japanese rice pilaf.

5
00:00:14.900 --> 00:00:16.880
Japanese rice pilaf?!

6
00:00:16.880 --> 00:00:18.040
Curses!

7
00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:20.210
What kind of rice pilaf is it?!

8
00:00:20.210 --> 00:00:22.120
<i>That's</i> what you're worried about?

9
00:00:22.680 --> 00:00:24.870
Is it a classic 
five-ingredient Japanese pilaf?

10
00:00:25.370 --> 00:00:28.130
Or a salmon and mushroom pilaf?

11
00:00:28.420 --> 00:00:31.430
Or maybe it's a baby sardine 
and seaweed pilaf!

12
00:00:31.430 --> 00:00:33.400
Why do you know so much 
about rice pilafs?

13
00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:35.380
Without further ado...

14
00:00:36.060 --> 00:00:39.630
Let us begin the torture, Princess.

15
00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:04.200
I forgot to turn on the rice cooker!

16
00:02:33.250 --> 00:02:35.000
'Tis Time for "Torture,"
Princess

17
00:02:38.110 --> 00:02:42.050
I can't believe I made 
such a basic mistake...

18
00:02:42.050 --> 00:02:44.290
I'm so sorry, Princess.

19
00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:46.560
Don't beat yourself up so much, Torture!

20
00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:48.560
Everyone makes mistakes.

21
00:02:48.560 --> 00:02:51.050
If you forgot to cook it, 
you can just do it now!

22
00:02:51.340 --> 00:02:53.280
Feel free to use one 
of my cell's sockets!

23
00:02:53.550 --> 00:02:54.900
Will that be all right?

24
00:02:54.900 --> 00:02:58.240
If I start it now, it'll take 
about fifty minutes to cook.

25
00:02:58.240 --> 00:02:59.770
Of course it's fine.

26
00:02:59.770 --> 00:03:03.770
We can spend our time waiting 
having a nice one-on-one chat.

27
00:03:03.770 --> 00:03:05.220
Princess...

28
00:03:06.150 --> 00:03:09.240
Is this what you'd call a torturous wait?

29
00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:11.630
Torturous wait?

30
00:03:16.850 --> 00:03:19.180
Oh, is that right?

31
00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:20.510
Uh-huh.

32
00:03:21.090 --> 00:03:24.010
Just the other day, the three of us 
were playing a fighting game...

33
00:03:24.780 --> 00:03:26.180
Keep practicing those combos!

34
00:03:26.180 --> 00:03:28.800
Get consistent with your short hops!

35
00:03:29.110 --> 00:03:33.750
At first, it was You-chan 
and I teaching In-chan...

36
00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:43.200
But before we knew it, 
In-chan was better than both of us.

37
00:03:44.710 --> 00:03:47.100
You must have done 
a good job teaching her.

38
00:03:47.100 --> 00:03:48.420
What? You think?

39
00:03:48.660 --> 00:03:50.940
Well, I'm sure that played a role.

40
00:03:50.940 --> 00:03:53.460
I <i>am</i> a legion commander, after all!

41
00:03:54.260 --> 00:03:57.830
Part of my job as commander 
was teaching new recruits.

42
00:03:57.830 --> 00:04:00.970
I didn't get many other chances 
to interact with people,

43
00:04:00.970 --> 00:04:03.570
so I had a lot of fun training them.

44
00:04:04.670 --> 00:04:07.930
I'd also befriend the few 
girls I met who were my age.

45
00:04:07.930 --> 00:04:12.190
We even used to have 
tea parties together.

46
00:04:14.770 --> 00:04:16.250
That sounds lovely.

47
00:04:16.650 --> 00:04:18.140
Speaking of which...

48
00:04:18.140 --> 00:04:21.000
A new recruit has joined us recently.

49
00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:22.150
Oh?

50
00:04:22.600 --> 00:04:27.070
It won't be for some time, 
but she'll be torturing you, too.

51
00:04:27.070 --> 00:04:29.850
Yeah? I'll look forward to it.

52
00:04:29.850 --> 00:04:32.580
It's funny how this 
sounds normal to me now.

53
00:04:33.700 --> 00:04:35.240
You know...

54
00:04:35.240 --> 00:04:39.430
We've never really had 
a nice, long talk like this before.

55
00:04:39.430 --> 00:04:41.960
I suppose we haven't.

56
00:04:41.960 --> 00:04:45.590
'Tis a common occurrence 
when you meet for work all the time.

57
00:04:45.590 --> 00:04:46.920
Guess so.

58
00:04:47.890 --> 00:04:52.410
We got to spend this time 
because you forgot to cook the rice.

59
00:04:52.410 --> 00:04:54.620
Maybe it was for the best, in a way.

60
00:04:56.550 --> 00:04:59.510
I had fun talking 
about all this stuff with you.

61
00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:01.150
I did, too.

62
00:05:04.310 --> 00:05:06.000
Looks like it's done.

63
00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:06.980
Indeed.

64
00:05:21.730 --> 00:05:22.960
Okay...

65
00:05:22.960 --> 00:05:24.940
Time to get to surrendering.

66
00:05:46.850 --> 00:05:50.480
<i>I'm glad I got to talk to Torture 
for so long today.</i>

67
00:05:50.800 --> 00:05:53.770
<i>And I managed to remember 
a lot about the past.</i>

68
00:05:54.870 --> 00:05:58.690
<i>Oh yeah, I forgot I used to keep 
a diary before I came here.</i>

69
00:05:59.560 --> 00:06:03.170
<i>I'm pretty sure I wrote in it the day 
before I was captured...</i>

70
00:06:06.390 --> 00:06:08.510
Is something wrong?

71
00:06:08.510 --> 00:06:09.590
No...

72
00:06:10.790 --> 00:06:13.710
<i>Huh? Did I remember to put my diary away?</i>

73
00:06:14.070 --> 00:06:17.480
<i>I put it back in the drawer 
and locked it up, didn't I?</i>

74
00:06:18.500 --> 00:06:20.980
<i>Did I? I did, didn't I?</i>

75
00:06:21.250 --> 00:06:22.400
Your Highness?

76
00:06:24.530 --> 00:06:29.070
<i>I can remember writing in it
but not putting it away.</i>

77
00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:35.470
<i>Did I leave it out on my desk?</i>

78
00:06:35.470 --> 00:06:38.990
<i>That'd mean anyone could read it 
if they entered my room!</i>

79
00:06:40.650 --> 00:06:42.000
<i>I can't let that happen!</i>

80
00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:43.910
<i>I need to do something about this!</i>

81
00:06:46.660 --> 00:06:49.430
'Tis time for torture, Princess.

82
00:06:49.430 --> 00:06:50.460
I yield!

83
00:06:50.460 --> 00:06:51.140
What?

84
00:06:51.140 --> 00:06:53.610
Torture hasn't brought anything out yet!

85
00:06:53.610 --> 00:06:55.770
The castle's west tower, fourth floor.

86
00:06:55.770 --> 00:06:58.770
The room at the very end. 
That's the weak point.

87
00:06:59.960 --> 00:07:01.190
Burn it down!

88
00:07:01.190 --> 00:07:02.390
Your Highness?!

89
00:07:02.390 --> 00:07:04.970
At least wait and see what it is 
before you surrender!

90
00:07:04.970 --> 00:07:07.740
Follow the proper surrender etiquette!

91
00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:10.580
No, what the hell 
is "surrender etiquette"?!

92
00:07:10.580 --> 00:07:14.820
Is there a reason you're 
so desperate to give in?

93
00:07:16.930 --> 00:07:18.610
You see...

94
00:07:20.130 --> 00:07:21.420
So that was it.

95
00:07:21.420 --> 00:07:24.150
You forgot to put your diary away?

96
00:07:24.150 --> 00:07:25.250
Yeah.

97
00:07:25.250 --> 00:07:28.350
I'd do anything to stop my diary 
from being read!

98
00:07:28.350 --> 00:07:29.750
The humiliation!

99
00:07:29.750 --> 00:07:32.220
Did you really forget to put it away?

100
00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:33.770
I'm not sure.

101
00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:37.970
Honestly, the possibility is low.

102
00:07:38.250 --> 00:07:41.250
But now, I can't get 
the idea out of my head!

103
00:07:43.120 --> 00:07:44.860
Burn it all down...

104
00:07:44.860 --> 00:07:47.830
Please don't wish 
for your homeland to burn down.

105
00:07:48.870 --> 00:07:52.080
I'm afraid burning 
the castle down is not an option.

106
00:07:52.790 --> 00:07:56.270
However, I can see if you'd be 
allowed to temporarily return.

107
00:07:56.270 --> 00:07:58.710
There's a chance they'd say yes to that?

108
00:07:58.710 --> 00:08:01.290
Why can't I remember if I put it away?

109
00:08:01.290 --> 00:08:05.020
I can remember picking up 
the book I use as my diary...

110
00:08:05.830 --> 00:08:08.130
By diary, do you perhaps mean...

111
00:08:08.130 --> 00:08:11.080
a book with the Royal 
Empire's emblem on it?

112
00:08:11.390 --> 00:08:13.580
Huh? How do you know that?

113
00:08:13.580 --> 00:08:15.860
Among your possessions...

114
00:08:15.860 --> 00:08:17.460
Oh! That's right!

115
00:08:18.050 --> 00:08:21.950
I put it in my bag since we 
were setting out on a long expedition!

116
00:08:22.350 --> 00:08:24.900
And then I was captured, which means...

117
00:08:24.900 --> 00:08:25.910
That's right.

118
00:08:25.910 --> 00:08:28.530
It's in the Hellhorde's custody now.

119
00:08:28.530 --> 00:08:29.510
Huh? Wait, then...

120
00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:32.230
I'm so glad I didn't leave it on my desk!

121
00:08:32.500 --> 00:08:36.580
If anyone had read it, 
I'd pass out foaming at the mouth!

122
00:08:36.580 --> 00:08:37.850
I see now.

123
00:08:37.850 --> 00:08:40.170
So that book was your diary.

124
00:08:40.170 --> 00:08:41.080
Eh?

125
00:08:41.080 --> 00:08:45.700
I thought it was a poetry collection 
since it was so romantic.

126
00:08:50.380 --> 00:08:51.420
Ah.

127
00:08:51.420 --> 00:08:53.540
So you really <i>did</i> read it?

128
00:08:53.540 --> 00:08:55.820
You have the wrong idea, Princess!

129
00:08:55.820 --> 00:08:57.760
In case it held any imperial information,

130
00:08:57.760 --> 00:09:01.970
I had to go through all of your belongings 
with our intelligence unit!

131
00:09:01.970 --> 00:09:04.610
May I ask how much of her diary you read?

132
00:09:06.910 --> 00:09:08.910
Please accept my apologies.

133
00:09:08.910 --> 00:09:11.230
We read through it in its entirety.

134
00:09:14.670 --> 00:09:15.700
Your Highness?

135
00:09:20.420 --> 00:09:21.370
Your Highness?

136
00:09:22.130 --> 00:09:23.260
Your Highness!

137
00:09:28.730 --> 00:09:30.040
Princess!

138
00:09:28.730 --> 00:09:30.040
Your Highness!

139
00:09:31.400 --> 00:09:34.300
Your Highness!

140
00:09:34.300 --> 00:09:37.800
Your Highness!

141
00:09:38.220 --> 00:09:40.760
The torture was called off, 
so here is the unused...

142
00:09:41.300 --> 00:09:43.380
Ankake sauce over fried rice.

143
00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:52.610
Is it to your liking?

144
00:09:56.060 --> 00:09:58.370
It's so gooey.

145
00:10:01.310 --> 00:10:05.210
I wish the princess 
could have tried some.

146
00:10:08.960 --> 00:10:11.000
'Tis Time for "Torture,"
Princess

147
00:10:14.130 --> 00:10:18.050
Sunday
Inki's Place

148
00:10:18.050 --> 00:10:19.220
Gourmandization 
Classroom

149
00:10:20.230 --> 00:10:22.220
What are you up to over there?

150
00:10:24.300 --> 00:10:27.730
I'm on torture duty tomorrow.

151
00:10:27.730 --> 00:10:32.750
My torture is showing her a movie, 
and stopping just when it gets good.

152
00:10:32.750 --> 00:10:34.730
I'm picking out the movie.

153
00:10:34.730 --> 00:10:36.580
Oh?

154
00:10:36.580 --> 00:10:40.060
I'm trying to pick one based on 
what Princess-chan likes,

155
00:10:40.370 --> 00:10:42.460
but it's proving to be tough.

156
00:10:43.960 --> 00:10:45.580
<i>She's enjoying herself.</i>

157
00:10:46.450 --> 00:10:49.290
Why not just go with your favorite movie?

158
00:10:50.490 --> 00:10:53.990
I'm scared to pick my favorite!

159
00:10:53.990 --> 00:10:55.470
Scared?

160
00:10:55.470 --> 00:11:00.500
I really, really love 
my favorite movie...

161
00:11:01.080 --> 00:11:03.880
If Princess-chan doesn't like it...

162
00:11:03.880 --> 00:11:06.310
This movie's not very good.

163
00:11:06.310 --> 00:11:09.000
Just show her another 
one if that happens.

164
00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:11.140
It's not as simple as that!

165
00:11:11.140 --> 00:11:14.460
Wh-When someone rejects 
your favorite thing...

166
00:11:14.460 --> 00:11:16.910
It's like having your 
heart's spine snapped in half!

167
00:11:16.910 --> 00:11:18.650
Does your heart <i>have</i> a spine?

168
00:11:18.650 --> 00:11:24.420
B-Besides, my favorite movies aren't
 the movies I recommend.

169
00:11:24.420 --> 00:11:29.400
I-I like my all-time favorite, 
but its reputation's not great.

170
00:11:27.290 --> 00:11:29.410
Ranking

171
00:11:27.290 --> 00:11:29.410
Reviews

172
00:11:29.710 --> 00:11:35.250
I-It'd objectively score around a sixty 
if you deducted points for its flaws.

173
00:11:35.250 --> 00:11:40.140
B-But when awarding points based on 
my personal opinion, it gets a million!

174
00:11:41.090 --> 00:11:44.670
<i>You don't see In-chan being this honest 
with herself too often.</i>

175
00:11:44.670 --> 00:11:46.350
Anyway, I'm scared.

176
00:11:46.350 --> 00:11:47.670
I can't.

177
00:11:47.670 --> 00:11:50.480
I'm just too scared to do it.

178
00:11:50.950 --> 00:11:55.480
Still, isn't it fun when other 
people like the things you do?

179
00:11:57.450 --> 00:12:02.730
I don't know much about them, 
but isn't Princess-chan a movie buff?

180
00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:11.320
P-Princess...

181
00:12:11.320 --> 00:12:13.820
Time for your torture...

182
00:12:13.820 --> 00:12:15.670
What's wrong, In-chan?

183
00:12:15.670 --> 00:12:17.670
Are you feeling sick?

184
00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:19.930
I...

185
00:12:20.210 --> 00:12:21.010
I?

186
00:12:22.860 --> 00:12:26.220
I brought a movie for us to watch!

187
00:12:54.410 --> 00:12:56.800
This movie's not very good.

188
00:12:58.890 --> 00:13:00.420
Um...

189
00:13:00.710 --> 00:13:03.060
That movie was great, In-chan!

190
00:13:04.660 --> 00:13:09.820
The plot wasn't exactly easy to follow, 
but its overall ambience was impeccable!

191
00:13:10.250 --> 00:13:12.230
I know, right?!

192
00:13:12.230 --> 00:13:16.550
Wait, the scene with the milk 
being poured at the beginning...

193
00:13:16.550 --> 00:13:18.610
Yeah, yeah! You got it!

194
00:13:18.610 --> 00:13:20.760
It was symbolizing Aurelia's fate!

195
00:13:20.760 --> 00:13:21.820
It <i>was</i>?!

196
00:13:22.160 --> 00:13:24.180
Let's rewatch it! One more time!

197
00:13:24.180 --> 00:13:25.580
Yeah, sure!

198
00:13:25.690 --> 00:13:29.570
Inki had a lot of fun

199
00:13:30.140 --> 00:13:31.550
Really?

200
00:13:31.550 --> 00:13:33.950
I'm glad Princess-chan 
ended up liking it.

201
00:13:33.950 --> 00:13:34.920
Yeah.

202
00:13:35.190 --> 00:13:38.400
I couldn't have done it 
without you encouraging me.

203
00:13:41.450 --> 00:13:44.840
Inki, what was today's secret?

204
00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:45.840
Ah.

205
00:13:46.520 --> 00:13:49.280
It was so much fun, you forgot to ask?

206
00:14:06.810 --> 00:14:09.980
Yeah! So awesome!

207
00:14:09.980 --> 00:14:13.160
Your Highness, what is it you've 
been binge-watching lately?

208
00:14:13.160 --> 00:14:14.790
A foreign drama series!

209
00:14:14.790 --> 00:14:16.940
I borrowed it from In-chan!

210
00:14:16.940 --> 00:14:19.860
It's very exciting 
and full of cliffhangers.

211
00:14:19.860 --> 00:14:22.920
Okay, next up is the sixth 
and final volume!

212
00:14:23.280 --> 00:14:24.180
Huh?

213
00:14:24.170 --> 00:14:26.420
Life 
      Seeker

214
00:14:24.170 --> 00:14:26.420
Life 
      Seeker

215
00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:26.020
Volume six is missing.

216
00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:28.960
Did In-chan forget to include it?

217
00:14:31.670 --> 00:14:33.120
Princess-chan.

218
00:14:33.120 --> 00:14:37.870
Looks like you watched 
the foreign drama I recommended.

219
00:14:37.870 --> 00:14:38.880
Yeah!

220
00:14:38.880 --> 00:14:41.520
I'm dying to watch the rest.

221
00:14:42.390 --> 00:14:45.060
Princess, time for your torture.

222
00:14:45.060 --> 00:14:47.370
C-Come again?!

223
00:14:47.370 --> 00:14:51.150
Last time, the torture 
completely slipped my mind.

224
00:14:51.150 --> 00:14:54.050
You had to go back and ask, didn't you?

225
00:14:54.050 --> 00:14:56.630
I won't be making 
the same mistake this time.

226
00:14:56.970 --> 00:15:00.780
If you want to watch the rest, 
you'll have to tell me a secret.

227
00:15:00.780 --> 00:15:02.000
I get it now!

228
00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:06.170
Both that movie and this foreign drama 
were part of your torture!

229
00:15:06.170 --> 00:15:08.420
Our friendship all this time...

230
00:15:08.420 --> 00:15:10.430
was that a lie as well?!

231
00:15:10.430 --> 00:15:13.220
Nope, our friendship's the real deal.

232
00:15:14.300 --> 00:15:15.460
Your Highness?!

233
00:15:15.710 --> 00:15:18.890
We may be friends, but this is my job.

234
00:15:18.890 --> 00:15:21.310
Damn you and your professionalism!

235
00:15:21.310 --> 00:15:23.530
But don't think you've won!

236
00:15:23.530 --> 00:15:25.540
I'm dying to know what happens next,

237
00:15:25.540 --> 00:15:29.940
but I'm the Princess and Commander 
of the Imperial Third Legion!

238
00:15:29.940 --> 00:15:33.770
My real-life exploits are far more
exciting than any foreign drama!

239
00:15:33.770 --> 00:15:36.280
I will never yield to the likes of you!

240
00:15:36.280 --> 00:15:40.470
Besides, I can watch 
the rest whenever I get out of here.

241
00:15:40.470 --> 00:15:42.480
Now I have more to look forward to!

242
00:15:42.890 --> 00:15:44.660
I see...

243
00:15:45.550 --> 00:15:46.750
Princess-chan.

244
00:15:47.040 --> 00:15:50.160
Who's your favorite 
character in this show?

245
00:15:50.160 --> 00:15:51.060
Huh?

246
00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:54.340
I guess it'd be Carrie.

247
00:15:54.340 --> 00:15:55.730
Carrie?

248
00:15:55.730 --> 00:15:57.600
She's the main character's daughter.

249
00:15:58.010 --> 00:16:01.280
He's spent many years 
fighting as a mercenary,

250
00:16:01.280 --> 00:16:05.640
but his dream is to return home to his 
wife and daughter one day.

251
00:16:06.680 --> 00:16:08.760
Carrie's so cute, isn't she?

252
00:16:08.760 --> 00:16:10.020
You said it.

253
00:16:10.020 --> 00:16:13.110
We only see her in flashbacks, 
but man, she's adorable!

254
00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:17.790
Will we ever get to see what 
Carrie looks like now, all grown up?

255
00:16:17.790 --> 00:16:20.790
I hope she gets to live happily 
with the main character.

256
00:16:21.150 --> 00:16:24.410
Oh yeah, talking about 
Carrie reminds me...

257
00:16:25.140 --> 00:16:29.750
Do you remember the assassin 
in a gas mask from volume five?

258
00:16:29.750 --> 00:16:31.630
Huh? Sure...

259
00:16:36.680 --> 00:16:38.920
Don't spoil me!

260
00:16:38.920 --> 00:16:40.350
What?

261
00:16:40.350 --> 00:16:44.680
Hearing you talk about Carrie
 reminded me of the assassin.

262
00:16:44.680 --> 00:16:46.140
Not bad, In-chan.

263
00:16:46.140 --> 00:16:48.130
Your Highness! Calm yourself!

264
00:16:48.130 --> 00:16:49.200
Damn you!

265
00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:51.110
That's playing dirty!

266
00:16:51.110 --> 00:16:52.540
But I won't...

267
00:16:52.540 --> 00:16:54.080
The main character's favorite food.

268
00:16:55.540 --> 00:16:57.510
The piano back home.

269
00:16:57.510 --> 00:16:59.310
The left-handed artisan.

270
00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:00.030
Stop it!

271
00:17:00.030 --> 00:17:02.810
Stop rattling off what 
sounds like key phrases!

272
00:17:02.810 --> 00:17:03.930
It's working, In-chan!

273
00:17:03.930 --> 00:17:05.760
The torture's doing a real number on her!

274
00:17:08.100 --> 00:17:11.510
But it's true that the piano back home...

275
00:17:11.510 --> 00:17:13.250
wasn't covered in any dust.

276
00:17:13.250 --> 00:17:14.560
Ah!

277
00:17:14.560 --> 00:17:17.160
I can't stop my brain from using 
the phrases to connect the dots!

278
00:17:17.160 --> 00:17:20.890
The Sherlock inside my mind! My Holmes!

279
00:17:19.630 --> 00:17:20.890
Please calm down!

280
00:17:20.890 --> 00:17:24.760
A master detective like Holmes is nowhere 
to be found in that head of yours!

281
00:17:28.660 --> 00:17:30.870
The seven dolls.

282
00:17:30.870 --> 00:17:32.360
The aunt's birthday.

283
00:17:32.360 --> 00:17:34.140
Stop! Please stop!

284
00:17:34.140 --> 00:17:36.330
I want to enjoy it spoiler-free!

285
00:17:36.330 --> 00:17:38.270
The clock in the plaza.

286
00:17:40.820 --> 00:17:43.060
I'll talk...

287
00:17:43.060 --> 00:17:44.170
Your Highness?!

288
00:17:45.160 --> 00:17:47.620
The princess 
confessed

289
00:17:52.700 --> 00:17:56.000
I'm so happy that he got to live 
with Carrie again!

290
00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:59.500
The assassin didn't have 
anything to do with her!

291
00:17:58.780 --> 00:18:01.910
Looks like the two 
of you have similar tastes.

292
00:18:03.220 --> 00:18:06.210
Nothing beats a happy ending!

293
00:18:08.580 --> 00:18:10.160
I see.

294
00:18:10.860 --> 00:18:14.440
So this is the king's 
favorite horror movie.

295
00:18:14.700 --> 00:18:19.780
Knowing the enemy's tastes may 
prove important to winning this war.

296
00:18:22.490 --> 00:18:24.860
Then I shall have to watch it.

297
00:18:25.510 --> 00:18:29.150
However, a bath will have to come first.

298
00:18:30.900 --> 00:18:36.580
If I watch a horror film first, 
I'll be too scared to take one.

299
00:18:38.340 --> 00:18:42.340
'Tis Time for "Torture,"
Princess

300
00:18:38.340 --> 00:18:40.490
I get it now...

301
00:18:42.890 --> 00:18:47.800
Sakura-chan, thanks for coming 
with me to shop for torture devices.

302
00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:50.350
No, it's the least I could do!

303
00:18:50.590 --> 00:18:55.330
<i>I spent all my time studying the blade, 
which left me with no other strengths.</i>

304
00:18:55.330 --> 00:18:57.440
<i>Shopping's about all 
I can do to help out.</i>

305
00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:01.090
<i>I wish there was some way 
I could be more useful.</i>

306
00:19:01.490 --> 00:19:03.790
Well, best of luck with that.

307
00:19:03.790 --> 00:19:05.950
I'll be heading back for now.

308
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:07.540
Sakura-chan.

309
00:19:08.570 --> 00:19:11.890
I was planning to make pancakes today.

310
00:19:11.890 --> 00:19:13.580
Could I ask you to assist me?

311
00:19:14.610 --> 00:19:15.830
You'd be okay with that?

312
00:19:16.110 --> 00:19:18.540
I would appreciate your help very much.

313
00:19:20.300 --> 00:19:23.430
Hellholm
 Communal
 Kitchen

314
00:19:23.780 --> 00:19:27.010
There's no need to mix so vigorously.

315
00:19:27.460 --> 00:19:29.890
L-Like this?

316
00:19:29.890 --> 00:19:32.270
Yes, you're doing great.

317
00:19:36.860 --> 00:19:38.140
How's it look?

318
00:19:38.440 --> 00:19:39.770
Right as rain.

319
00:19:47.390 --> 00:19:49.570
The batter's starting to bubble!

320
00:19:49.570 --> 00:19:51.920
It should be just about ready.

321
00:19:52.230 --> 00:19:54.370
Time to flip it!

322
00:19:59.970 --> 00:20:02.170
I did it on my first try!

323
00:20:02.170 --> 00:20:03.430
Impressive work.

324
00:20:03.430 --> 00:20:05.750
First the whisk, now this.

325
00:20:05.750 --> 00:20:07.880
You're great with utensils.

326
00:20:08.420 --> 00:20:12.350
When it comes to handling swords, 
I was always best with a dagger.

327
00:20:12.350 --> 00:20:15.630
Maybe tools this size 
just come naturally to me.

328
00:20:16.050 --> 00:20:17.410
I see.

329
00:20:17.410 --> 00:20:19.820
So this is where your strengths lie.

330
00:20:20.640 --> 00:20:22.430
My strengths...

331
00:20:25.880 --> 00:20:28.120
The pancakes are all done.

332
00:20:28.120 --> 00:20:29.660
They look great!

333
00:20:29.660 --> 00:20:31.900
Yes, they look scrumptious.

334
00:20:31.900 --> 00:20:35.290
Your very first torture implements.

335
00:20:35.290 --> 00:20:36.370
Yes.

336
00:20:36.740 --> 00:20:39.310
I hope they like these...

337
00:20:41.050 --> 00:20:44.120
'Tis time for torture, Princess.

338
00:20:44.460 --> 00:20:49.290
I'm the Princess and Commander 
of the Imperial Third Legion.

339
00:20:49.600 --> 00:20:52.770
No matter the torture, 
I will never give in!

340
00:20:55.010 --> 00:20:57.190
Looks yummy!

341
00:20:59.290 --> 00:21:01.320
Delicious!

342
00:21:01.650 --> 00:21:04.690
The princess
confessed

343
00:21:10.210 --> 00:21:11.590
Sakura-chan.

344
00:21:11.590 --> 00:21:14.990
The torture target said they 
were delicious.

345
00:22:50.800 --> 00:22:53.800
Series Total

